      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Quality of Water</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Drugs Are in the Water. Does it Matter?'' (April 3): The general tone of Cornelia Dean's article on pharmaceutical and personal care products being detected in the water is that if they don't affect us, they're not really a problem. Since marine ecosystems are already damaged from overfishing, habitat destruction, toxic chemicals and conventional pollutants, they certainly are being further impaired by the effects from pharmaceuticals released into the water. Whether or not these chemicals are hurting humans, the answer to her question is: Yes, it does matter.</p>
        <p>Judith S. Weis  Newark</p>
      </block>
